\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 In addition to text underlay for `lyrics' introduced in the previous lesson, Calliope provides four other ways to add text to a document:\par
\pard\tx360\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi-230\sb80\sa0\li360\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 ·	Object labels\par
\pard\tx360\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi-230\sb80\sa0\li360\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 ·	System headers\par
\pard\tx360\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi-230\sb80\sa0\li360\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 ·	Staff headers\par
\pard\tx360\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi-230\sb80\sa0\li360\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 ·	Page titles (running headers and footers)\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 All these may contain RichText, a standard format used by other NeXTStep applications.  With RichText it is possible to apply arbitrary font styles (to individual characters if necessary) and paragraph layouts.  Variables (such as page numbers) may be embedded in running headers and footers.  Let's look at each type of text object in turn.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\keepn\fi0\sb240\sa80\li0\ri0\f1\fs32\b1\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Labels\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Object labels (or just \i labels\i0 ) are associated with any staff object (note, rest, clef, signature, barline, block).  Labels may contain any RichText and may be positioned with an arbitrary relative offset from the object with which it is associated.  Labels are \i not\i0  a good way to add lyrics or punctuation (\i i.e.\i0  accents, articulation marks, dynamics marks. \i etc.\i0 ) to an object, as there are other more convenient ways to do these.  However, labels are useful in adding editorial commentary or other instructions that are connected with a particular staff object.\par
