\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\keepn\fi0\sb240\sa80\li0\ri0\f1\fs32\b1\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Staff Headers\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Staff Headers are text boxes that are associated with particular staves.  They are useful for instructions such as \b\i Allegro\b0\i0  and \b\i Tutti\b0\i0 , and for labelling instrumental parts (\i e.g.\i0  Horn IV).  In this example we shall add a staff headers to each staff of the Sonata introduced in Lesson 1:\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 {{\NeXTGraphic4 graphic_24.eps \width9020\height2080
}¬} \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 First we need to add a left indent of 1 inch to the system to make room for the headers.  To do this, get the System Inspector (Command-click on the system's marker), enter \fs24\f1\b0\i0 1\f0  in the \fs24\f1\b0\i0 L\f1 eft Indent\f0  field, and press \fs24\f1\b0\i0 S\f1 ET\f0 .  Then use the \fs24\f1\b0\i0 S\f1 ystem\f2\f2 ®\f1\f1 A\f1 djust to Width\f0  command to re-adjust the music on the shorter line.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 To make a staff header, press the Staff Header Tool, which looks like this:{{\NeXTGraphic4 graphic_16.tiff \width720\height720
